dom-animationevent-animationevent.name: AnimationEvent
dom-animationevent-animationevent.summary: The AnimationEvent() constructor returns a newly created AnimationEvent, representing an event in relation with an animation.
dom-animationevent-animationevent.title: AnimationEvent()

dom-animationevent-animationname.name: animationName
dom-animationevent-animationname.summary: The AnimationEvent.animationName read-only property is a DOMString containing the value of the animation-name CSS property associated with the transition.
dom-animationevent-animationname.title: AnimationEvent.animationName

dom-animationevent-elapsedtime.name: elapsedTime
dom-animationevent-elapsedtime.summary: The AnimationEvent.elapsedTime read-only property is a float giving the amount of time the animation has been running, in seconds, when this event fired, excluding any time the animation was paused. For an animationstart event, elapsedTime is 0.0 unless there was a negative value for animation-delay, in which case the event will be fired with elapsedTime containing (-1 * delay).
dom-animationevent-elapsedtime.title: AnimationEvent.elapsedTime

dom-animationevent-pseudoelement.name: pseudoElement
dom-animationevent-pseudoelement.summary: The AnimationEvent.pseudoElement read-only property is a DOMString, starting with '::', containing the name of the pseudo-element the animation runs on. If the animation doesn't run on a pseudo-element but on the element, an empty string: ''.
dom-animationevent-pseudoelement.title: AnimationEvent.pseudoElement

interface-animationevent.name: AnimationEvent
interface-animationevent.summary: The AnimationEvent interface represents events providing information related to animations.
interface-animationevent.title: AnimationEvent

interface-csskeyframerule.name: CSSKeyframeRule
interface-csskeyframerule.summary: The CSSKeyframeRule interface describes an object representing a set of style for a given keyframe. It corresponds to the contains of a single keyframe of a @keyframes at-rule. It implements the CSSRule interface with a type value of 8 (CSSRule.KEYFRAME_RULE).
interface-csskeyframerule.title: CSSKeyframeRule

interface-csskeyframesrule.name: CSSKeyframesRule
interface-csskeyframesrule.summary: The CSSKeyframesRule interface describes an object representing a complete set of keyframes for a CSS animation. It corresponds to the contents of a whole @keyframes at-rule. It implements the CSSRule interface with a type value of 7 (CSSRule.KEYFRAMES_RULE).
interface-csskeyframesrule.title: CSSKeyframesRule

interface-cssrule.name: CSSRule
interface-cssrule.summary: The CSSRule interface represents a single CSS rule. There are several types of rules, listed in the Type constants section below.
interface-cssrule.title: CSSRule

eventdef-animationevent-animationcancel.name: animationcancel_event
eventdef-animationevent-animationcancel.summary: The animationcancel event is fired when a CSS Animation unexpectedly aborts. In other words, any time it stops running without sending an animationend event. This might happen when the animation-name is changed such that the animation is removed, or when the animating node is hidden using CSS. Therefore, either directly or because any of its containing nodes are hidden.
eventdef-animationevent-animationcancel.title: Document: animationcancel event

eventdef-animationevent-animationcancel.name: onanimationcancel
eventdef-animationevent-animationcancel.summary: The onanimationcancel property of the GlobalEventHandlers mixin is the EventHandler for processing animationcancel events.

safari.notes: The event handler is exposed but will not actually be called unless both the "Web Animations" and "CSS Animations via Web Animations" preferences are enabled.

safari_ios.notes: The event handler is exposed but will not actually be called unless both the "Web Animations" and "CSS Animations via Web Animations" preferences are enabled.

eventdef-animationevent-animationcancel.title: GlobalEventHandlers.onanimationcancel

eventdef-animationevent-animationend.name: animationend_event
eventdef-animationevent-animationend.summary: The animationend event is fired when a CSS Animation has completed. If the animation aborts before reaching completion, such as if the element is removed from the DOM or the animation is removed from the element, the animationend event is not fired.
eventdef-animationevent-animationend.title: Document: animationend event

eventdef-animationevent-animationend.name: onanimationend
eventdef-animationevent-animationend.summary: The onanimationend property of the GlobalEventHandlers mixin is the EventHandler for processing animationend events.
eventdef-animationevent-animationend.title: GlobalEventHandlers.onanimationend

eventdef-animationevent-animationend.name: animationend_event
eventdef-animationevent-animationend.summary: The animationend event is fired when a CSS Animation has completed. If the animation aborts before reaching completion, such as if the element is removed from the DOM or the animation is removed from the element, the animationend event is not fired.
eventdef-animationevent-animationend.title: HTMLElement: animationend event

eventdef-animationevent-animationiterati.name: animationiteration_event
eventdef-animationevent-animationiterati.summary: The animationiteration event is fired when an iteration of a CSS Animation ends, and another one begins. This event does not occur at the same time as the animationend event, and therefore does not occur for animations with an animation-iteration-count of one.
eventdef-animationevent-animationiterati.title: Document: animationiteration event

eventdef-animationevent-animationiterati.name: onanimationiteration
eventdef-animationevent-animationiterati.summary: The onanimationiteration property of the GlobalEventHandlers mixin is the EventHandler for processing animationiteration events.

eventdef-animationevent-animationiterati.name: animationiteration_event
eventdef-animationevent-animationiterati.summary: The animationiteration event is fired when an iteration of a CSS Animation ends, and another one begins. This event does not occur at the same time as the animationend event, and therefore does not occur for animations with an animation-iteration-count of one.

eventdef-animationevent-animationstart.name: animationstart_event
eventdef-animationevent-animationstart.summary: The animationstart event is fired when a CSS Animation has started. If there is an animation-delay, this event will fire once the delay period has expired. A negative delay will cause the event to fire with an elapsedTime equal to the absolute value of the delay (and, correspondingly, the animation will begin playing at that time index into the sequence).
eventdef-animationevent-animationstart.title: Document: animationstart event

eventdef-animationevent-animationstart.name: onanimationstart
eventdef-animationevent-animationstart.summary: An event handler for the animationstart event. This event is sent when a CSS Animation starts to play.
eventdef-animationevent-animationstart.title: GlobalEventHandlers.onanimationstart

keyframes.name: keyframes
keyframes.summary: The @keyframes CSS at-rule controls the intermediate steps in a CSS animation sequence by defining styles for keyframes (or waypoints) along the animation sequence.

firefox.notes: @keyframes is unsupported in scoped stylesheets in Firefox (bug 830056).

keyframes.title: @keyframes

animation-delay.name: animation-delay
animation-delay.summary: The animation-delay CSS property specifies the amount of time to wait from applying the animation to an element before beginning to perform the animation.

firefox.notes: Before Firefox 57, Firefox does not repaint elements outside the viewport that are animated into the viewport with a delay. This bug affects only some platforms, such as Windows.

animation-delay.title: animation-delay

animation-direction.name: animation-direction
animation-direction.summary: The animation-direction CSS property sets whether an animation should play forward, backward, or alternate back and forth between playing the sequence forward and backward.
animation-direction.title: animation-direction

animation-duration.name: animation-duration
animation-duration.summary: The animation-duration CSS property sets the length of time that an animation takes to complete one cycle.

ie.notes: Once the element has loaded, changing the value of this property has no effect.

animation-duration.title: animation-duration

animation-fill-mode.name: animation-fill-mode
animation-fill-mode.summary: The animation-fill-mode CSS property sets how a CSS animation applies styles to its target before and after its execution.
animation-fill-mode.title: animation-fill-mode

animation-iteration-count.name: animation-iteration-count
animation-iteration-count.summary: The animation-iteration-count CSS property sets the number of times an animation sequence should be played before stopping.
animation-iteration-count.title: animation-iteration-count

animation-name.name: animation-name
animation-name.summary: The animation-name CSS property specifies the names of one or more @keyframes at-rules describing the animation or animations to apply to the element.
animation-name.title: animation-name

animation-play-state.name: animation-play-state
animation-play-state.summary: The animation-play-state CSS property sets whether an animation is running or paused.
animation-play-state.title: animation-play-state

animation-timing-function.name: animation-timing-function
animation-timing-function.summary: The animation-timing-function CSS property sets how an animation progresses through the duration of each cycle.
animation-timing-function.title: animation-timing-function

animation-timing-function.name: easing-function
animation-timing-function.summary: The <easing-function> CSS data type denotes a mathematical function that describes how fast one-dimensional values change during animations. This lets you vary the animation's speed over the course of its duration.
animation-timing-function.title: <easing-function>

animation.name: animation
animation.summary: The animation shorthand CSS property applies an animation between styles.

webview_android.notes: The animation-fill-mode property is not supported in Android browsers below 2.3.

animation.title: animation
